de.interactive_instruments.etf.testdriver

Interface TestResultCollector

  • All Superinterfaces:
    BasicTestResultCollector, de.interactive_instruments.Releasable

    public interface TestResultCollector
extends BasicTestResultCollector
    The TestResultCollector is used to report failures and messages during a test run as well as adding information about the control flow, attachments and logging messages (info, debug, error) which are written to a log path and linked from the test task result. The TestResultCollector is exposed by a test driver, injected into a test engine and consumed during a test run by a test driver adapter. A class that implements the TestResultCollector should realize a state machine and could throw IllegalStateExceptions if operations are called in the wrong order. Complex / external types are avoided in order to facilitate easy integration.

      • endWithSkippedIfTestCasesFailed

        boolean endWithSkippedIfTestCasesFailed(java.lang.String... testCaseIds)
                                 throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException,
                                        java.lang.IllegalStateException
        If a Test Case depends on other TestCases this method must be called after the recording of a Test Case has been started. If any of those TestCases have the status TestResultStatus.FAILED or TestResultStatus.SKIPPED, the recording of the Test Case will be stopped by invoking end(String, int) with the status TestResultStatus.SKIPPED.
        Parameters:
        testCaseIds - Test Case EIDs
        Returns:
        true if the Test Case has been skipped, false otherwise
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if test already has been ended
        java.lang.IllegalStateException - if the current Test Case already has been ended or the recording of a TestCase has not been started
